<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="1016" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1016">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">622.116/121: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-19T18:00:00-05:00">August 19, 1940—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>188. Reference to Department’s 116, August 17, 11 a.m. The Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs and the Director General of exchange control out of
                            city. Matter will be further discussed tomorrow or Wednesday and
                            indications are that application of exchange authorizations will be
                            postponed for 2 weeks or longer.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>